         <abstract>
            <p>The anti-Semitic emperor involved in the talmudic narrative about Ketiah Bar Shalom is identified as Hadrian. Evidence is adduced from the language of the text, a Latin wordplay transposed into Aramaic, the characterization of the emperor and the important thematic elements in the story.</p>
         </abstract>
